## ⚠️ Key Risks

> [!WARNING]
> **68 Signal/Slot Rewiring** — The biggest single task. Every `PySide6.QtCore.Signal` in 14 files must become a Python-native event emitter or asyncio queue. This touches `brain.py`, `ai_client.py`, `voice_listener.py`, `tts_manager.py`, `system_monitor.py`, `proactive_engine.py`, `notification_router.py`, `memory_store.py`, `sentence_buffer.py`, `calendar_manager.py`, `task_runner.py`, `hotkey_listener.py`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Two-process startup** — Electron must spawn Python, poll `/health`, then show UI. On quit, must kill Python cleanly. The `QTimer`-based timers in `brain.py`, `system_monitor.py`, `proactive_engine.py` must become `asyncio` timers or threading timers.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **QThread → asyncio migration** — `AIThread`, `VoiceThread`, `TTSThread`, `HotkeyThread` use `QThread`. These become either `asyncio.Task` or `threading.Thread` with queue-based communication.

