## 🛠️ Implementation Phases

### Phase 1: Python Backend API Layer (3-4 days)

**Goal:** Decouple backend from PySide6 so it can serve any frontend.

#### [NEW] `src/api/event_bus.py`
Simple async pub/sub replacing all `Signal`/`Slot` usage:
```python
class EventBus:
    async def emit(self, event: str, data: Any) -> None: ...
    def on(self, event: str, handler: Callable) -> None: ...
```

#### [NEW] `src/api/server.py`
FastAPI server:
- `WS /ws/chat` — user query → streaming tokens → done
- `WS /ws/state` — broadcast animation state changes
- `GET/POST /settings` — config CRUD
- `GET/DELETE/PUT /memory` — memory CRUD
- `GET /health` — provider health checks
- `POST /voice/start`, `POST /hotkey/clip`

#### [MODIFY] All 14 PySide6-importing files
- Replace `Signal` → `event_bus.emit()`
- Replace `@Slot` → plain methods
- Replace `QTimer` → `asyncio` timers or `threading.Timer`
- Replace `QThread` → `threading.Thread` + queues
- **No logic changes** — only communication layer

#### [MODIFY] `main.py` → `src/api/main.py`
68 signal connections → WebSocket message routing + event bus wiring.

